Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.io

Class ParseTree

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.io.ParseTree
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<ParseTree>
public class ParseTree extends Object implements Iterable<ParseTree>
A parse tree is the result of successfully matching a sequence of tokens to a pattern. Parse trees are an intermediate step in parsing an object and will usually be given to a builder to create an object.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

  • Constructor Details

    • ParseTree

      public ParseTree(Pattern pattern, ImmutableList<Token> tokens, ParseTree... children)
      Constructs a new parse tree. Note that child trees that match non-symbols will be flattened one level. For example, if one of the children given is a parse tree matching a list, rather than adding that tree as a child, that tree's children will be added as children of this tree.
      Parameters:
      pattern - the pattern that matches the sequence of tokens
      tokens - the sequence of tokens
      children - the results of matching any smaller patterns that appear inside this tree's pattern

    • ParseTree

      Parameters:
